Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Peel the @garlic cloves{2}. Add the potatoes and the garlic cloves to the boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into your pan.

Next, pop a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Season the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once hot, lay the chicken in the pan skin-side down, fry until the skin is golden, ~{5%minutes}. Turn, cook for ~{1%minute} on the flesh side to seal the meat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Transfer to a large #baking tray{} skin-side up and roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Trim the root of the @pak choi{2} and separate the leaves. Halve the @plums{2}, remove the stone and slice the flesh of each plum into 12 thin wedges. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. When the chicken has had ~{10%minutes} in the oven, add the bok choy to the baking tray around the chicken breasts (not covering), drizzle a little @oil{} over the top, season and return to the oven for the remaining cooking time, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Pop your frying pan back on medium-high heat (no need to wash). Add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry, then add the plums to the pan and fry, turning them every minute until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Pour in the @water{75%ml} and add the @sugar{1}, @chicken stock paste{10} and @hoisin sauce{32}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat slightly and gently simmer until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it thickens too much.

Once cooked, set aside.

Once the chicken and bok choy is cooked, remove from your oven, cover the tray with some #foil{} and leave to rest for ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once the potatoes are cooked and back in their pan, add the spring onion along with a @butter{knob} and splash of @?milk{}. Season with salt and pepper and then mash with a #potato masher{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm. Reheat the plum sauce with a splash of water if you need to. Pile the mash onto the #plates{}, top with the chicken breast and share the bok choy alongside. Spoon the hoisin plum sauce over the chicken and enjoy!